channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Hackers Target Iranian Banks in 'Massive Cyber Attack'
Stefanik calls on NY official to resign for comparing Trump to 'rabid dog' after assassination attempt
item.description: House GOP Conference Chair Elise Stefanik is demanding that a local elected official in her district resign after making inflammatory comments about the Trump shooting.

item.title: Comer Seeks Info on Trump Assassination Attempt Censorship
item.description: House Oversight Committee Chair James Comer, R-Ky., is seeking information from Meta and Google on potential censorship related to the July assassination attempt on former President Donald Trump.

item.title: Olympic Boxer Imane Khelif Sues for 'Harassment'
Florida AG demands answers after report found nearly 100 potential terrorist migrants released by Biden admin
item.description: Florida Attorney General Ashley Moody sent a scathing letter to DHS Secretary Alejandro Mayorkas demanding answers on the whereabouts of migrants included on a terror watchlist.

item.title: Harris' Ukraine Policy Unclear, Relations Strained
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris' approach to Ukraine in its war against Russia should she win the presidency remains unclear.

item.title: Adam Kinzinger, Eric Swalwell Tag Team for Most Ridiculous Response to Musk-Trump Spaces Event
Top House committee demands Mayorkas fork over docs after Biden admin freezes migrant flight program
item.description: The House Homeland Security Committee is investigating the pause of the Cuba, Haiti, Nicaragua and Venezuela parole program, saying they are "deeply concerned" by revelations.

item.title: NC GOP Chair to Newsmax: Trump Has 'Great Record' in State
item.description: Donald Trump has a "great record" of winning in North Carolina, a state that will prove vital to his chances this fall, state GOP Chairman Jason Simmons told Newsmax ahead of the former president's rally in Asheville Wednesday afternoon.

item.title: Thailand's Constitutional Court Removes Prime Minister From Office in Shocking Ruling
Walz defends his military record, praises JD Vance's, in 1st solo campaign stop
item.description: Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz, tapped by VIce President Kamala Harris to be her running mate, has been on the defensive about his military service record amid waves of criticism.

item.title: Caroline Sunshine to Newsmax: Harris 'Plagiarizing' Trump
item.description: Caroline Sunshine, deputy communications director for former President Donald Trump's 2024 campaign, told Newsmax on Wednesday that Vice President Kamala Harris is "plagiarizing" Trump's policies that appeal to voters.

item.title: Another Influencer Comes Forward Exposing Harris Campaign Paying for Support
Americans view Harris as more honest than Trump, but trust her less on economy, immigration: poll
item.description: A new poll has found that American adults view Vice President Kamala Harris as a more honest person than former President Trump, but are less likely to trust her when it comes to handling key issues such as the economy and immigration.

item.title: Miami Mayor to Newsmax: Must Convince More Hispanics to Vote GOP
item.description: The effort to convince more Hispanics to vote Republican is crucial not just for this presidential race, but for a possible generation shift that will carry over into future elections, Miami Mayor Francis Suarez told Newsmax on Wednesday.
